y
x \le y \lt \infty
f_X(x)=\int_0^\infty f_{XY}(x,y) dy=\int_x^\infty \lambda^2\exp(-\lambda y)dy = \lambda \exp(-\lambda x)
f_Y(y)=\int_0^\infty f_{XY}(x,y) dx=\int_0^y \lambda^2\exp(-\lambda y)dx = \lambda^2 y \exp(-\lambda y)
f_X(x) f_Y(y) \ne f_{XY}(x,y)
Z=X/(Y-X)
Y
Z
 P(Z\le a)= P(X\le a(Y-X))= P(X\le aY/(1+a))=\int_0^\infty dy \big(\int_0^{ay/(1+a)} f_{XY}(x,y) dx\big)=\int_0^\infty ay/(1+a) \lambda^2\exp(-\lambda y) dy=a/(1+a)\int_0^\infty y\lambda^2\exp(-\lambda y)dy=a/(1+a) 
 P(Y\le b)=\int_0^b \lambda^2 y \exp(-\lambda y)dy 
 P(Z\le a, Y\le b)=a/(1+a)\int_0^b\lambda^2\exp(-\lambda y)dy 
 P(Z\le a, Y\le b)=P(Y\le b)P(Z\le a) 
